reviews.review: I like this one probably the most but the story was all too predictable. The biggest plot surprise in movie history was in The Empire Strikes Back. I guess nothing can ever compare but I wish something shocking had happened this time around. Nonetheless, I did enjoy this finale in the trilogy and recommend every fan to watch it.
What I heard about the movie was horrible, but when I saw it in the theater, I loved it. I am a Star Wars fan that loved Rise of Skywalker. Very good end to the 42 year old saga.

This movie displays the skywalker's long lasting battle between good and evil in a story of epic proportions. It may not bring a lot that is new to the table but it enriches the saga and pays honor to what has come before. The hate this movie is getting is undeserved. Disney's most obvious problem with its sequel trilogy is it's lack of written plan. Giving it lesser direction than previous installments. But I believe J. J. Abrams did the absolute best he could in trying to tie together what he started in 7. Let alone the conclusion of all 9 films. But when rewatching the original trilogy and sequel trilogy, you will see that this new group of films is not alone in its flaws. And if that's what you're looking for when going in to see this movie. That's all your going to find. But if you go in optimistic, you won't be disappointed by the close of this 40 year old story and it's formidable foe.

This was a fine ending to the cronicole that started for me at a drive-in in 1977 watching the adventures of Luke, Lia, Han, and Chewi. And more than 40ty years later watching the fine conclusion to that saga.
Great way to end an epic series!!
Great ending to a fantastic lifetime series.
Honestly, I have no words at the moment.
A muddled mess of fan service and back pedaling with no real ideas and no risks taken. Definitively proved that Disney had no real plan for these from the beginning. A real wasted opportunity.
Great movie. Great sound in the theater

Its like if your favorite football team made it to the Super Bowl made a few cool plays but still lost 10K-14. Its like Disney didnt have any plan for this trilogy and let the director for the last Jedi do whatever with no consideration that theres going to be a movie following his. JJ did the best he could with what he had but it felt forced and nothing felt earned.
